  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to evaluate the efficacy of motivational interviewing (MI) on adherence to
      exercises and on levels of pain and incapacity in patients who engage in physiotherapy for
      low back pain. Sixty patients attending a 15-day program of physiotherapy for low back pain
      were allocated to experimental (EG) and control groups (CG). A regular treatment of
      physiotherapy with at-home exercises is offered to all participants. On day seven, MI is
      applied to the EG. The CG receives an anti-inflammatory information program.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
